{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CT4UD4xHh4cSa1bE3huGLU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 7)\n     2→\n     3→### 0-5-4-run-command-integration — dev-story (2026-03-20T08:12Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **run.ts at exactly 300 lines**: Was 358 originally, NFR9 requires ≤300. Extracting `countStories` and `buildSpawnArgs` to run-helpers.ts got it to exactly 300. Any future changes need more extraction.\n     6→- **Pre-existing TS errors in test files**: Loosely-typed `vi.fn()` mocks don't match strict type signatures. Exists across many test files — not introduced by this story.\n     7→- **Coverage gap in polling interval**: The 5-second `setInterval` callback in run.ts (lines 207-228) is not directly tested. Helper functions it calls are tested independently with 100% coverage.\n     8→- **run-helpers.test.ts at 303 lines**: Slightly over 300-line NFR9 limit. Test files typically exempt.\n     9→\n    10→### 0-5-4-run-command-integration — code-review (2026-03-20T08:20Z)\n    11→\n    12→- **MEDIUM: Misleading test name** (`defaults to 3` but asserts `10`) — fixed.\n    13→- **LOW (not fixed): run.ts branch coverage 70.23%** — uncovered branches are error-handling catch blocks (prompt write failure, JSON parse failure). Reasonable to leave untested.\n    14→- **LOW (not fixed): coverage-summary.json confusion** — file contains Jest-format results, not istanbul coverage data. Pre-existing.\n    15→- **No integration test for full stream-json → Ink pipeline** — all tests mock the renderer.\n    16→- **Coverage: 96.65% overall, all 111 files above 80% floor. 2722 tests pass.**\n    17→\n    18→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dabb15c1-c215-43f4-93fb-96b1eac1157b","uuid":"c23b8fe8-2fdc-428e-a1fd-fa5364d5456e","timestamp":"2026-03-20T08:33:14.465Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-20 (Session 7)\n\n### 0-5-4-run-command-integration — dev-story (2026-03-20T08:12Z)\n\n- **run.ts at exactly 300 lines**: Was 358 originally, NFR9 requires ≤300. Extracting `countStories` and `buildSpawnArgs` to run-helpers.ts got it to exactly 300. Any future changes need more extraction.\n- **Pre-existing TS errors in test files**: Loosely-typed `vi.fn()` mocks don't match strict type signatures. Exists across many test files — not introduced by this story.\n- **Coverage gap in polling interval**: The 5-second `setInterval` callback in run.ts (lines 207-228) is not directly tested. Helper functions it calls are tested independently with 100% coverage.\n- **run-helpers.test.ts at 303 lines**: Slightly over 300-line NFR9 limit. Test files typically exempt.\n\n### 0-5-4-run-command-integration — code-review (2026-03-20T08:20Z)\n\n- **MEDIUM: Misleading test name** (`defaults to 3` but asserts `10`) — fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed): run.ts branch coverage 70.23%** — uncovered branches are error-handling catch blocks (prompt write failure, JSON parse failure). Reasonable to leave untested.\n- **LOW (not fixed): coverage-summary.json confusion** — file contains Jest-format results, not istanbul coverage data. Pre-existing.\n- **No integration test for full stream-json → Ink pipeline** — all tests mock the renderer.\n- **Coverage: 96.65% overall, all 111 files above 80% floor. 2722 tests pass.**\n\n","numLines":18,"startLine":1,"totalLines":18}}}
